# Please using the following guidelines to format all commit messages:
#
#   <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#   <EMPTY LINE>
#   <body>
#   <EMPTY LINE>
#   <footer>
#
#
# Note:
#    - Header is a single line with a max of 65 characters which 
#contains a succinct description of the change made. Contains a 
#type, an optional scope, and #a subject.
#       <type>: describes the kind of change that was made, and 
#should be one of the follow categories
#           * feat (feature)
#           * fix (bug fix)
#           * docs (documentation)
#           * style (formatting)
#           * refactor
#           * test (addition of missing tests)
#           * chore (maintenance)
#       <scope>: specifying the place of the change
#       <subject>: a short description
#           * imperative, present tense language: "change" not 
#"changed"/"changes"
#           * do not capitalize first letter
#           * no ending "."
#   - Body should include the motivation for the change and the 
#contrast this with previous behavior and must be phrased in 
#imperative present tense.
#   - Footer should contain any information about Breaking Changes 
#and is also the place to reference GitHub issues that the commit 
#closes 
